  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Get your chicken breasts and chop them into chunks. Pop them in a bowl."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Make your marinade. Place your garlic, ginger, soy sauce, sesame oil, peanuts, cumin, coconut milk, the juice from your lime and peanut butter into a food processor, then whizz until smooth."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Pour your marinade over your chicken and give it a good toss until all coated. Marinade in the fridge for 2 hours."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Meanwhile, soak your wooden skewers in water."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Heat your grill to high."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Remove your chicken from the marinade and place onto your skewers."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Place your chicken under the grill and cook for 20-30 mins until your chicken is all tender and charred around the edges. You’ll need to turn them occasionally to ensure that they cook easily."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Whilst your chicken grills, make your slaw. Get a vegetable peeler and use it to peel large strips of carrot and cucumber. Grate your cabbage. Finely chop your coriander."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Add your vegetable ribbons and cabbage to a bowl and mix with your rice wine vinegar, lime juice, most of your coriander, and black and white sesame seeds."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Heat your remaining coconut milk and sesame oil and give them a good whisk."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Add your peanut butter, soy sauce, fish sauce, chilli flakes, garlic powder and honey to the pan and whisk again until all lovely and smooth."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Serve your skewers on top of rice along with your slaw. Top with crushed peanuts, coriander, chilli flakes and a drizzle of your satay sauce. Eat up."
    }
  ],
